{
  "texts": [
    "Our fine-tuned frame-semantic parsing model performed much better on frame and argument identification for both case studies.",
    "A key observation was GPT-4o-mini's tendency to over-predict frame occurrence in sentences.",
    "Performance improved significantly when we constrained the analysis to only the first predicted frame (GPT-4o-mini*).",
    "Similar patterns emerged in frame element predictions, where GPT-4o-mini frequently predicted frame elements that do not exist in the frame definition or are not used in the input sentence.",
    "Examples of these are provided in Appendix D.2."
  ]
}